						<summary>

						<p>On a stone set up in the Sakalēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1174, Uttarāyaṇa Saṅkrānti.</p>						

						<p>Damaged. Seems to record the gift of land for burning a perpetual lamp to the god Kēśavadēva by Manuma-Nāyaka and Nārapa-Nāyaka, for the merit of their parents.</p>						

						</summary>
